# --- Rust ---
/target/
**/target/
Cargo.lock.bak
*.rs.bk

# --- Generated by the Roze compiler itself (roze build / roze run) ---
# Every .roze file you build emits a same-named .java source file and
# .class bytecode file right next to it. These are build outputs, not
# source, and should never be committed -- same idea as not committing
# target/.
*.class
# NOTE: we intentionally do NOT ignore *.java globally, since some tools
# (e.g. IDE integration) may keep hand-written .java interop files. If you
# want the compiler's generated .java files ignored too, uncomment:
# /*.java

# --- Debug/scratch files produced while developing the compiler itself ---
debug_tokens.rs
debug_tokens.roze

# --- IDE / editor ---
.idea/
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
*.iml
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Logs & temp ---
*.log
*.tmp
*.bak

# --- Language Server / tooling caches ---
.roze-cache/
